commands
--------

user commands:
--------------
git config --global user.name '-username'
git config --global user.email '-email'
git config --global core.editor "code --wait --new-window" = to set vs code as code editor for git credentials
git config --edit --global = to display username and email in an editor


Fresh Repository
----------------
git init
git add '-file-name'
or
git add .
git commit -m "-message"
git branch -M main
git remote add origin -url-link
git push -u origin main

Existing Repository:
---------------------
git init
git status = to check whether changes are visible or not
git add '-file-name'
or 
git add .
git commit -m "-message"
git status = to check whether changes are staged or not
git push -u origin main


Branching the Existing Repository:
----------------------------------

git branch = gives all the branches(main = present)

git branch -C -branch-name = to create new branch

git checkout -branch-name = to shift to newly created branch

git branch = to show on which branch, you are currently on

git add .

fit commit -m "-message"

git push origin HEAD = to push the changes to newly created branch

common commands:
---------------

git log --oneline = display all the commit messages belonging to that repo

git reset --hard Head~1 = to go back to previous comitted changes

